  "prompt": "How do I make clothes in Roblox?",
  "response": "To make clothes in Roblox, you need to follow these steps:\n\n### 1. **Design Your Clothing**\nFirst, design your clothing using a graphics editor like Photoshop, GIMP, or any other program that supports layers and transparent PNG files. The dimensions for the clothing template are 585 pixels wide by 559 pixels tall. You can download the clothing templates from the Roblox Create page.\n\n### 2. **Create a Roblox Account**\nIf you don't have one already, sign up for a Roblox account. You'll need a Builders Club membership to upload clothing.\n\n### 3. **Access the Create Page**\nLog in to your Roblox account and go to the **Create** page. Click on the **Creations** tab, then select **Shirts**, **Pants**, or **T-Shirts** depending on what you're creating.\n\n### 4. **Upload Your Design**\n- **Shirts and Pants**: Click on the **Manage my experiences** button, then click on **Shirts** or **Pants**. Click the **Choose File** button to select your PNG file and then click **Upload**.\n- **T-Shirts**: Click on **T-Shirts** and then click the **Create a T-Shirt** button. Choose your PNG file and upload it.\n\n### 5. **Configure Your Item**\nGive your item a name and a description. You can also set a price if you want to sell it. Click **Upload** to finalize the process.\n\n### 6. **Test Your Clothing**\nAfter uploading, you can test your clothing in Roblox Studio by applying it to a character model to see how it looks in-game.\n\n### 7. **Publish Your Clothing**\nOnce you're satisfied with the design, publish your clothing. It will appear in your inventory and can be worn by your avatar or sold to other players if you've set a price.\n\n### Additional Tips\n- **Templates**: Always start with the official Roblox templates to ensure your design fits correctly on the avatar.\n- **Transparency**: Use transparency in your design to create cutouts or intricate designs.\n- **Resolution**: Make sure your design is clear and not pixelated at the required resolution.\n\nIf you follow these steps, you'll be able to create and upload custom clothing to Roblox. Happy designing!",
